1
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:09,920
DOCTOR: Hello, Ponds.
Checking in. How are you?

2
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:11,680
Really?

3
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:14,360
Not much to report.

4
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:18,120
Surfed the Fire Falls of Florinel 9.

5
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:20,680
Not deliberately,
Just the easiest way out.

6
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,440
Met Mata Hari in a Paris hotel room.

7
00:00:27,240 --> 00:00:28,920
What an interesting woman!

8
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,160
(HIP HOP MUSIC PLAYING)

9
00:00:31,280 --> 00:00:33,840
Laid down some backing vocals.

10
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,560
I should be with you any day now,
literally any day.

11
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,560
Helmic regulator's playing up.

12
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:41,320
Can't get the temporal steering right.

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,760
Oh, dear! I appear to have collided
with ancient Greece.

14
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:46,560
(DOCTOR YELLING)

15
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:48,680
-(BEEPING)
-AMY: The Doctor.

16
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,920
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

17
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,760
-(EXCLAIMS) Stop everything!
-What's going on?

18
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:16,880
-Doctor, bedroom!
-We have a rule about the bedroom.

19
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:18,400
No one on this planet is safe right now.

20
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:20,080
We have to solve this
before it's too late.

21
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,160
Get your clothes on!

22
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:23,080
If we move fast enough,
we at least stand a chance.

23
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:24,800
And you have no idea
what I'm talking about, do you?

24
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:28,840
-BOTH: No.
-Oh, helmic regulator again!

25
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:31,440
Too early! Wrong point! As you were!

26
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:33,120
Doctor, you can't just go like that.

27
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,200
What's happening? Don't we need to know?

28
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:37,840
Popped up in the wrong order.
Easy mistake to make.

29
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:39,800
Nothing to alarm you,
forget I was ever here.

30
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,440
I'll be back soon enough,
I would've thought.

31
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:44,560
Everything's fine, pretty much.
Don't worry about the future.

32
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,800
The future's really...

33
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:49,000
safe.

34
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,160
Really, really safe.

35
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:55,560
(DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE)

36
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:57,480
(WHISPERS) Sleep well.

37
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,400
-(TARDIS WHOOSHING)
-I really hate it when he does that.

38
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,600
Whoa!

39
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:39,280
Out of the way, Mr Pond.

40
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,600
What? Why not?

41
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:52,520
May I be of any assistance?

42
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:56,320
-Ood on the loo.
-Yeah.

43
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:18,480
Ood! Yes!
I was wondering where he'd got to.

44
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,760
I thought he'd just gone
for a walk in the Tardis.

45
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:24,320
Must've wandered off
when I popped in the other night...

46
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,360
If it was the other night.

47
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:30,000
You know, I rescued him from the middle
of the Androvax Conflict.

48
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,120
I was taking him back
to the Ood Sphere.

49
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,400
Anyway, he's not being a nuisance,
is he?

50
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:45,240
-Enjoy your workday experience.
-Thanks.

51
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:53,600
Doctor. Doctor!

52
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:58,160
He, um...
He seems to think that he's our butler.

53
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:01,080
He's conditioned to serve.
You know the best thing is

54
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:04,360
let him do just that,
I'll come and pick him up tonight.

55
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,920
Whenever "tonight” is.

56
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,240
(ALARM BLARING)

57
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:09,080
Oh, no! Gotta go!

58
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,800
Power drain's threatening
to cause the Tardis to implode.

59
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:14,400
Oh no, that's bad. Why is it doing that?
No, no, no! Don't do that!

60
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,840
Your infusions.
How else may I be of service?

61
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,840
- I feel so guilty.
-You just eat your breakfast.

62
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,480
BOTH: Mmm!

63
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:46,760
Ponds. Me again.
Sorry about the gaps in communications.

64
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:50,400
Dropped your Ood back home.
Reconnected it to the hive mind.

65
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:53,040
Helmic regulator's still not working.

66
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,600
Got hit by an arrow at Hastings Hill.

67
00:04:55,680 --> 00:05:00,000
Also, rode a horse through
11th-century Coventry.

68
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:03,840
Also, I think I may have
accidentally invented pasta.

69
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,480
Ah! Mmm...

70
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,600
I popped 'round but you were out,
which is fine.

71
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:20,000
Everything's all right, isn't it?
With you two?

72
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,400
Of course it is.

73
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:26,880
Ponds, always fine.
Just worrying unnecessarily.

74
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:30,360
Anyway, just call me
if you need me. Okay?

75
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,880
Toodle pip!

76
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,840
(BUZZING)

77
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,920
(BLEEPS)

78
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
AUTOMATED VOICE: Message deleted.

79
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:56,480
We need you, Raggedy Man.

80
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:00,840
I need you.

